      <h2>SDE Methodology: The Gold Standard for Medical Practice Valuation</h2>
      <p>The <strong>Seller's Discretionary Earnings (SDE)</strong> method is the most widely accepted approach for valuing medical practices. SDE represents the total financial benefit a single owner-operator derives from the business.</p>

      <h3>How SDE is Calculated:</h3>
      <div class="calculation-box">
        <h4>SDE Formula:</h4>
        <p><strong>SDE = Net Income + Owner's Salary + Discretionary Expenses + Non-recurring Expenses</strong></p>
      </div>

      <h3>Key Components of SDE:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Net Income:</strong> Bottom-line profit after all expenses</li>
        <li><strong>Owner's Salary:</strong> Compensation taken by the practice owner</li>
        <li><strong>Discretionary Expenses:</strong> Personal expenses run through the business</li>
        <li><strong>Non-recurring Expenses:</strong> One-time costs that won't continue</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

